news.title: Greater Noida authority auctions nine commercial plot for Rs 533 crore
news.para: GNIDA recently auctioned 9 commercial plots for Rs 533 crore, against a reserve price of Rs 458 crore. Adamant Construction and Nirala World were key winners, with Nirala World planning a commercial project. Earlier, three residential plots were auctioned for Rs 521 crore against a reserve price of Rs 262 crore.

news.title: House sales in Turkey surge 37.3% in September 2024
news.para: Mortgaged sales climbed 87.4% in September to 15,825 units while sales of new houses and flats rose by 47.1% in the same period, the data showed.

news.title: China's new home prices drop 5.8% in September 2024
news.para: In annual terms, new home prices were down 5.8% from a year earlier, deeper than a 5.3% slide in August, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data. Reuters also reported prices fell 5.7%, which was due to an automated rounding off of figures.

news.title: Vietnam's Truong My Lan convicted of fraud in anti-corruption case
news.para: Truong My Lan was already convicted in April by the same Ho Chi Minh City court of fraud amounting to UDS 12.5 billion - nearly 3 per cent of the country's gross domestic product - in a separate case and sentenced to death by lethal injection.

news.title: Charter Hall and Hostplus increase bid for Hotel Property Investments to $506 million
news.para: Charter Hall Retail REIT, managed by the property investor, and Hostplus have now sweetened the offer to A$3.85 from A$3.65 per Hotel Property share it does not already own.

news.title: China's property investment falls 10.1% in first nine months of 2024
news.para: Property sales by floor area in January-September fell 17.1% from a year earlier, compared with a 18.0% slump in January-August.

news.title: Bengaluru metro's extended green line to begin by month-end
news.para: In preparation for this, the corporation has written to the Urban Development Department to confirm the date of the launch. Sources said that all construction work is complete, and all tests have been successfully conducted.

news.title: Hyderabad: Drone survey done in Vikarabad for digital master plan
news.para: Vikarabad is among 20 municipalities in Telangana with over 50,000 population selected for creating a Geographical Information System (GIS)-based master plan under the Atal Mission for Rejuvenation and Urban Transformation (AMRUT) 2.0 of the Union ministry of housing and urban affairs.

news.title: Hyderabad IT corridor faces groundwater crisis despite heavy rainfall
news.para: According to groundwater department data, areas such as Kukatpally, Serilingampally, Ramachandrapuram, and Rajendranagar have taken the most beating with the average depth to water level (DTWL) here touching 17.51 metres in Sept.

news.title: Gujarat quarry operators call off strike after government assurance
news.para: The quarry association stated that all the quarries started work on Thursday, and supply will return to normal soon. However, the real estate industry said they faced huge losses due to the strike, and most construction projects were likely to miss their targets ahead of Diwali.

news.title: Madurai civic body announces 6% property tax hike
news.para: The hike is part of the Tamil Nadu Urban Local Bodies Rules, 2023, which mandates annual property value revisions based on either the average Gross State Domestic Product (GSDP) growth over the past five years or by 6%, whichever is higher, unless a general revision occurs.

news.title: AAIJI Group acquires 50 acres land in Dholera for Rs 150 crore
news.para: AAIJI Group plans to develop 3BHK villas, plots and retail spaces. Till date, the company has invested over Rs 100 crore in five projects in Dholera.

news.title: IBC may introduce voluntary group insolvency mechanism soon
news.para: The framework will be a part of Insolvency & Bankruptcy Code (IBC) amendments that the corporate affairs ministry could introduce in the winter session of Parliament, likely in December, they said

news.title: SC allows demolition of 41 illegal buildings in Agrawal Nagari, Mumbai
news.para: ​​The occupants, who were given a 24-hour notice by the VVMC on July 2, had sought relief from the Bombay High Court, which extended the eviction deadline to Oct 30 but refused to halt the demolition.

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels Paradiso's tower A declared unfit for living
news.para: The recent audit revealed significant structural deterioration in Tower A, primarily because of severe corrosion caused by high chloride content and poor-quality concrete — similar to issues found in the other towers. Tower A comprises 64 flats, 60 of which are occupied.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt directs administrations to form panels to implement new lift act
news.para: The legislation was approved by the state cabinet in July to control the rising accidents due to lifts and escalators in urban areas.

news.title: Lucknow: ED arrests Sai Construction and Builders' partner in loan fraud case
news.para: The ED initiated the probe against Tyagi based on an FIR registered by the CBI against M/s Sai Construction and Builders, Ghaziabad, its partners, and others under Sections IPC, 1860, and the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988, for alleged loan fraud.

news.title: Hyderabad: I-T department conducts searches at Anvitha Real Estate Group
news.para: Searches were also conducted at the offices of two directors, Atchuta Rao Boppana and Anup Boppana. Income tax officials inspected the registered office of Anvitha Infra Projects Private Limited in Raidurg, Gachibowli.

news.title: Prestige Estates sales bookings down 43% at Rs 4,022 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: ​​In a regulatory filing on Thursday, Prestige Estates informed that it recorded sales of Rs 4,022.6 crore during the July-September quarter against Rs 7,092.6 crore in the year-ago period.
